There are three facets to an organization's culture, and they are: The degree to which an organization values and rewards innovation and judicious risk-taking is one indicator of this dimension. In this regard, we might look to Google's famous 20% time policy, under which workers are free to spend 20% of their time on non-essential side projects. In business, "attention to detail" is adhering to a standard of exactness and thoroughness in all tasks. Tesla is a company that excels in this area because it pays close attention to detail throughout production. The level to which an organization is dedicated to the successful completion of defined objectives is one indicator of outcome orientation. Amazon is a company that exhibits this quality because of their dedication to meeting performance goals and enhancing their business processes on a regular basis. 